7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 474, L.D. 732, “An Act to Prohibit
10 Copyrights for Works of State Government”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Prohibit Copyrights for Works of Certain State Government Departments
13 and Agencies'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 1 MRSA §30 is enacted to read:
17 §30. Copyright for work of department or agency of the State prohibited
18 A work of a department or agency of the State may not be afforded copyright
19 protection, including under 17 United States Code or any subsequent federal law. This
20 section does not apply to goods sold or products offered for sale by a department or agency
21 of the State and does not preclude a department or agency of the State from receiving and
22 holding a copyright transferred to a department or agency of the State by assignment,
23 bequest or otherwise or a copyright of a work of a department or agency of the State existing
24 prior to the effective date of this section.
25 As used in this section, "department or agency of the State" does not include
26 prekindergarten to grade 12 public schools, the Maine State Museum, the Maine
27 Community College System, the University of Maine System or any other quasi-
28 independent state entity as defined in Title 5, section 12021, subsection 5.'
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, amends the bill by
3333 specifying that a work of a department or agency of the State may not be afforded copyright
3344 protection, including under Title 17 of the United States Code or any subsequent federal
