COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 474, L.D. 732
315 law. The amendment excludes goods sold or products offered for sale by a department or
326 agency of the State and does not preclude a department or agency of the State from
337 receiving and holding a copyright transferred to a department or agency of the State by
348 assignment, bequest or otherwise or a copyright of a work of a department or agency of the
359 State existing prior to the effective date of this section.
6 The amendment also clarifies that the term "department or agency of the State" does
7 not include prekindergarten to grade 12 public schools, the Maine State Museum, the Maine
8 Community College System, the University of Maine System or any other quasi-
9 independent state entity as defined in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 12021,
10 subsection 5.
11 The amendment also removes section 2 of the bill, which eliminates the ability of the
12 Maine State Museum to receive copyright law protection for research and publications.
